article.description:
Janeth Arcain scored 22 points as the Houston
Comets beat the Miami Sol 69-60 Thursday night.
article.headline: Houston's 12-0 run early in second half sets tone

images.name: Arcain_Janeth  020725 inline
images.caption: Houston's Janeth Arcain goes over Miami's Betty Lennox for two of her game-high 22 points.

article.linkText: Hot-shooting Arcain scores 22 to lead Comets past Sol
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Janeth Arcain scored 22 points as the Houston
Comets beat the Miami Sol 69-60 Thursday night.

<photo1>

	   Arcain made nine of 14 shots from the floor, including 2-for-3 from
3-point range, as Houston swept the two-game season series from
Miami.

	   ''I was more comfortable and confident to make my shots,''
Arcain said. ''Miami came to play hard and I knew we needed to
respond to that. They came to win, but we played together and came
back when we had to.''

	   Tina Thompson added 18 points for the Comets (19-6), who have
won 10 in a row at home since losing their opener to defending WNBA
champion Los Angeles.

	   ''We're playing with a really sick Tina Thompson right now,''
Houston coach Van Chancellor said of Thompson's lingering illness
due to food poisoning. ''It's amazing that she was still able to
play as well as she did.''

	   Sheri Sam led the Sol (11-13) with 17 points.

	   Miami made 44 percent of its shots, but committed 17 turnovers
and was outrebounded 27-22.

	   After Sam put the Sol up 41-39 with an 11-foot jumper with 17:37
to go, Houston reeled off a 12-0 run to lead 51-41.

	   ''We had a good chance to take control after a good start to the
second half,'' Miami coach Ron Rothstein said. ''But we let them
have way too many second chances and they pulled away.''

	   Betty Lennox added 15 points for the Sol, but made just one of
her six 3-point attempts in 24 minutes.

	   ''Things just weren't falling for me,'' she said. ''Their
defense didn't take me out of the game at all. I had some wide open
shots and I didn't make the most of them when I had the chance.''

	   Houston took a 29-21 lead in the first half before Miami
responded with an 8-2 run to close to two points.

   Sandy Brondello scored four points during the run, closing the
gap to 31-29. But Arcain scored five points in the final 1:08 of
the half.
